column5: WD-40 is a great fish attractant too. I've never used it myself, but my lures sure could for less rust.
That has to be the simplest and best flow chart I have ever seen.
wd 40 and duct tape...what else could you possibly need
A hammer because if you can't fix it with a hammer it must be an electrical problem.
And this from the guy that does all my small engine repairs...???
Oh you don't have to worry Beans, I used WD40 in your lower unit and put duct tape over the fill/drain holes. I only use the hammer if I can't figure out what is wrong LOL
